Hippos have skin that becomes easily dehydrated, so  
during the daylight hours, when the sun is hot,  
hippos are generally seen in the water sleeping and  
socializing with the other members of their herd.  
They are excellent swimmers and can remain under  
water for up to five minutes. When partially  
submerged, only their eyes, ears, and nostrils are  
visible. 
 
